    Cumulative1 School Management System Privacy Policy

    Cumulative1 is committed to protecting the privacy of our users. This policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your information. We collect data necessary for system functionality, including student records, teacher information, and course data. This may include names, contact details, grades, and attendance.  

    We use this information to manage school operations, facilitate communication, and provide educational services. Access to this data is restricted to authorized personnel, including school administrators, teachers, and support staff, on a need-to-know basis. We implement security measures to prevent unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure of your information.

    We do not share your personal data with third parties except when required by law or with your explicit consent. We may use aggregated, anonymized data for statistical analysis and system improvement. We retain your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy or as required by legal obligations.  

    You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal information. If you have concerns about our data handling practices, please contact us. We may update this policy periodically, and we encourage you to review it regularly. By using Cumulative1, you consent to the terms of this privacy policy.

